TITLE: Beyond Meat COO, Who Allegedly Bit Man's Nose, Leaves Company
SUMMARY: The plant-based meat maker, which is reducing its workforce by nearly 20%, said its operating chief, who had been suspended after being arrested last month, was no longer with the company.

TITLE: UnitedHealth Boosts Earnings Forecast on Rising Revenue
SUMMARY: UnitedHealth Group raised its profit outlook for the year after posting a 12% increase in third-quarter revenue.

TITLE: Elon Musk Says SpaceX Can't Fund Ukraine Starlink Service Indefinitely
SUMMARY: The SpaceX and Tesla chief said the cost of maintaining Starlink terminals in Ukraine, where they have played a crucial role during the war, is approaching $20 million a month.

TITLE: Retail Spending Stalled in September
SUMMARY: Consumers were able to spend less at the pump, but they also cut outlays on big-ticket items amid high inflation and rising interest rates.

TITLE: U.K. Prime Minister Fires Treasury Chief, U-Turns on Taxes
SUMMARY: Prime Minister Liz Truss reversed crucial parts of her government’s tax plan, a major setback for the new leader after her plan to jolt the economy into growth unraveled in spectacular fashion following a backlash from financial markets and her party.

TITLE: China's Inflation Rises at Fastest Pace in Two Years
SUMMARY: China’s consumer inflation rate hit 2.8% in September, was driven in part by a sharp rise in food prices.

TITLE: They're the Two Biggest Stars in Sports. Nike Let One Get Away.
SUMMARY: The American shoe giant signed Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo to sponsorships at the dawn of their careers. Then it lost one.

TITLE: FDA Warns of Adderall Shortage Months After Patients Raised Concerns
SUMMARY: Demand for the medication has surged since the government made it easier to get through telehealth appointments.

TITLE: The Unraveling of Trevor Milton: "No Good Deed"
SUMMARY: In this season’s second episode, we talk to some of the investors in Trevor Milton’s early business ventures who say they suffered life-changing financial losses as Trevor’s star continued to rise.

TITLE: Superfast 5G Gadgets Are Off to a Slow Start
SUMMARY: Despite their huge potential, 5G-enabled internet-of-things devices aren’t ubiquitous yet

TITLE: All the Best Gear and Gadgets You Can Buy With $10,000
SUMMARY: Plus, four rad tools that will make you want to spend it all in one place

TITLE: Kroger, Albertsons in Talks to Create Supermarket Powerhouse
SUMMARY: The potential deal would combine the two largest supermarket operators in the U.S., creating a grocery giant with thousands of stores and one of the country’s biggest employers.

TITLE: Want to Get Ahead? Pick the Right Company
SUMMARY: The best places to advance your career, get groomed for bigger opportunities elsewhere and find job stability, as determined by a new study.

TITLE: U.S., Allies Negotiating Price Level for Russian Oil Cap
SUMMARY: The Group of Seven large advanced democracies, along with Australia, are working to put into place a plan ahead of a Dec. 5 deadline that would bar the use of financing, insuring and shipping services for Russian oil unless the oil is sold below a set price limit.

TITLE: Retirees Catch a Break With the Social Security COLA
SUMMARY: A 35-year-old index shows how inflation for the elderly has gone from above to below average.

TITLE: PC Buyers Curtail New Purchases as Pandemic Splurge Wanes
SUMMARY: Recession fears and high inflation contributed to one of the worst downturns in computer sales in decades.

TITLE: Nutanix Explores Sale After Receiving Takeover Interest
SUMMARY: The cloud-computing company is expected to target private-equity and industry players, according to people familiar with the matter.

TITLE: America's Red-Hot Warehouse Market Shows Signs of Cooling
SUMMARY: A pandemic-driven boom in warehousing demand is showing signs of slowing, as companies grow more cautious about leasing in an uncertain economy.
